<ArticleLayout
  title="Preparing for Your Cleaning Visit"
  description="Simple checklist to prepare for a professional carpet or upholstery cleaning visit: access, furniture, pets and parking."
>
  <p>To ensure a smooth and efficient visit, here is a quick checklist before our technician arrives:</p>

  <h2>1) Clear access to the entrance</h2>
  <p>We may need direct hose access from the truck to your door. Please keep the driveway or closest access point clear if possible.</p>

  <h2>2) Remove small fragile items</h2>
  <p>Please move lamps, plants, toys, and fragile objects away from the areas to be cleaned.</p>

  <h2>3) Heavy furniture guidelines</h2>
  <p>We can move many common items such as sofas and tables. For safety reasons, we do not move fully loaded bookcases, pianos, waterbeds, or complex electronic setups.</p>

  <h2>4) Secure pets during the visit</h2>
  <p>For safety, keep pets in a separate room while doors may remain partially open for equipment access.</p>
</ArticleLayout>
